{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21",
    "summary": "Source text for 2 Chronicles 21 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:1",
      "text": "And the chiefs of the people dwelt in Jerusalem: and the rest of the people cast lots, to bring one of every ten to dwell in Jerusalem the holy city, and nine parts in the other cities.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:2",
      "text": "And the people blessed all the men that volunteered to dwell in Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:3",
      "text": "Now these are the chiefs of the province who dwelt in Jerusalem, and in the cities of Juda; every man dwelt in his possession in their cities: Israel, the priests, and the Levites, and the Nathinim, and the children of the servants of Solomon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:4",
      "text": "And there dwelt in Jerusalem some of the children of Juda, and of the children of Benjamin. Of the children of Juda; Athaia son of Azia, the son of Zacharia, the son of Samaria, the son of Saphatia, the son of Maleleel, and some of the sons of Phares;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:5",
      "text": "and Maasia son of Baruch, son of Chalaza, son of Ozia, son of Adaia, son of Joarib, son of Zacharias, son of Seloni.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:6",
      "text": "All the sons of Phares who dwelt in Jerusalem were four hundred and sixty-eight men of might.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:7",
      "text": "And these were the children of Benjamin; Selo son of Mesulam, son of Joad, son of Phadaia, son of Coleia, son of Maasias, son of Ethiel, son of Jesia.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:8",
      "text": "And after him Gebe, Seli, nine hundred and twenty-eight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:9",
      "text": "And Joel son of Zechri was overseer over them: and Juda son of Asana was second in the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:10",
      "text": "Of the priests: both Jadia son of Joarib, and Jachin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:11",
      "text": "Saraia, son of Elchia, son of Mesulam, son of Sadduc, son of Marioth, son of Ætoth, was over the house of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:12",
      "text": "And their brethren doing the work of the house were eight hundred and twentytwo: and Adaia son of Jeroam, son of Phalalia, son of Amasi, son of Zacharia, son of Phassur, son of Melchia,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:13",
      "text": "and his brethren, chiefs of families, two hundred and forty-two: and Amasia son of Esdriel, son of Mesarimith, son of Emmer,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:14",
      "text": "and his brethren, mighty men of war, a hundred and twenty-eight: and their overseer was Badiel son of one of the great men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:15",
      "text": "And of the Levites; Samaia, son of Esricam,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:16",
      "text": "So the Lord stirred up the Philistines against Joram, and the Arabians, and those who bordered on the Æthiopians:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:17",
      "text": "Matthanias son of Micha, and Jobeb son of Samui,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:18",
      "text": "two hundred and eighty-four.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:19",
      "text": "And the porters; Acub, Telamin, and their brethren, a hundred and seventy-two.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:20",
      "text": "He was thirty and two years old when he began to reign, and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem. And he departed without honour, and was buried in the city of David, but not in the tombs of the kings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:22",
      "text": "And the overseer of the Levites was the son of Bani, son of Ozi, the son of Asabia, the son of Micha. Of the sons of Asaph the singers some were over the house of God,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:23",
      "text": "for so was the king's commandment concerning them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:24",
      "text": "And Phathaia son of Baseza was in attendance on the king in every matter for the people,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:25",
      "text": "and with regard to villages in their country district: and some of the children of Juda dwelt in Cariatharboc,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:26",
      "text": "and in Jesu,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:27",
      "text": "and in Bersabee:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:30",
      "text": "and their villages were Lachis and her lands: and they pitched their tents in Beersabee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:31",
      "text": "And the children of Benjamin dwelt from Gabaa to Machmas.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:second-chronicles.21.36",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "second-chronicles",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "2 Chronicles 21:36",
      "text": "And of the Levites there were divisions to Juda and to Benjamin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
